{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841526690,"sessionID":"ses_28798fd19ffeSktwOY78Gz36ZW","part":{"id":"prt_d78673f62001c0o18UURPR7iYU","messageID":"msg_d78672d80001aLqHmRDCm7G663","sessionID":"ses_28798fd19ffeSktwOY78Gz36ZW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a1cf67951a26476d91d7e758","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n6: - Go module path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n7: \n8: ## Architecture\n9: \n10: ### Overview\n11: \n12: The AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs are defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically through the Kubernetes API server.\n13: \n14: ```\n15: ┌─────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐\n16: │   API Server        │      │   Workload Manager  │\n17: │                     │      │                     │\n18: │  ┌───────────────┐  │      │  ┌───────────────┐  │\n19: │  │ agentruntimes │  │◄─────│  │ CREATE/UPDATE │  │\n20: │  └───────────────┘  │      │  └───────────────┘  │\n21: │  ┌───────────────┐  │      └─────────────────────┘\n22: │  │codeinterpreters│ │\n23: │  └───────────────┘  │\n24: └─────────────────────┘\n25:            │\n26:            ▼\n27: ┌─────────────────────┐\n28: │   client-go         │\n29: │   (generated)       │\n30: │                     │\n31: │ - Typed clients     │\n32: │ - Listers           │\n33: │ - Informers         │\n34: └─────────────────────┘\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Package Structure\n38: \n39: | File | Purpose |\n40: |------|---------|\n41: | `doc.go` | Package documentation, kubebuilder markers |\n42: | `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder |\n43: | `register.go` | Kind constants, resource helpers |\n44: | `types.go` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n45: | `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods (generated) |\n46: \n47: ## Data Structures\n48: \n49: ### AgentRuntime\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: // +genclient\n53: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n54: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n55: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n56: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n57: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n58: type AgentRuntime struct {\n59:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n60:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n61:     Spec              AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n62:     Status            AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n63: }\n64: \n65: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n66:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n67:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n68:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n69:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n70:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n71:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n72:     PodTemplate *PodTemplateSpec `json:\"podTemplate,omitempty\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n76:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n77:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n78: }\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ### CodeInterpreter\n82: \n83: ```go\n84: // +genclient\n85: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n86: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n87: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n88: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n89: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n90: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n91:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n92:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n93:     Spec              CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n94:     Status            CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n95: }\n96: \n97: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n98:     AuthMode *AuthMode `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n99:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n100:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n101:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n102:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n103:     Template ContainerTemplateSpec `json:\"template\"`\n104:     WarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n105: }\n106: \n107: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n108:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n109:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n110:     Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### Shared Types\n115: \n116: ```go\n117: type TargetPort struct {\n118:     Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n119:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"` // HTTP or HTTPS\n120:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n121:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n122: }\n123: \n124: type PodTemplateSpec struct {\n125:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n126:     Spec PodSpecSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n127: }\n128: \n129: type PodSpecSpec struct {\n130:     // Selective PodSpec fields: Containers, Volumes, ImagePullSecrets, etc.\n131:     // See proposal.md for full field list.\n132: }\n133: \n134: type ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n135:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n136:     Command []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n137:     Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n138:     Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n139:     Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n140:     RuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n141: }\n142: \n143: type AuthMode string\n144: \n145: const (\n146:     AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n147:     AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"\n148: )\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ## API Contracts\n152: \n153: ### AgentRuntime\n154: \n155: | Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n156: |-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n157: | `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n158: | `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n159: | `targetPort` | `[]TargetPort` | Yes | - | Port configuration array |\n160: | `podTemplate` | `*PodTemplateSpec` | No | - | Pod specification overrides |\n161: \n162: ### CodeInterpreter\n163: \n164: | Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n165: |-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n166: | `authMode` | `*AuthMode` | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n167: | `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n168: | `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout |\n169: | `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration |\n170: | `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n171: | `warmPoolSize` | `*int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n172: \n173: ### Status Subresource\n174: \n175: Both CRDs support `/status` subresource:\n176: - `conditions`: Kubernetes conditions array\n177: - `observedGeneration`: Last reconciled generation\n178: \n179: CodeInterpreter additionally includes:\n180: - `ready`: Boolean readiness indicator\n181: \n182: ## Error Handling\n183: \n184: ### CRD Validation\n185: \n186: Validation rules embedded via kubebuilder markers:\n187: \n188: ```go\n189: // Required field validation\n190: // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n191: \n192: // Default value handling\n193: // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n194: \n195: // Enum validation (AuthMode)\n196: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### Client-go Error Handling\n200: \n201: Standard Kubernetes client errors are handled by client-go:\n202: \n203: | Error Type | Handling |\n204: |------------|----------|\n205: | `errors.IsNotFound` | Resource does not exist |\n206: | `errors.IsAlreadyExists` | Resource already exists |\n207: | `errors.IsConflict` | Optimistic lock failure |\n208: | `errors.IsTimeout` | Operation timeout |\n209: \n210: Example usage:\n211: \n212: ```go\n213: agentRuntime, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n214: if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n215:     // Handle not found\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ## Testing Strategy\n220: \n221: ### Unit Tests\n222: \n223: #### Type Validation\n224: \n225: ```go\n226: func TestAgentRuntimeSpecValidation(t *testing.T) {\n227:     tests := []struct {\n228:         name    string\n229:         spec    AgentRuntimeSpec\n230:         wantErr bool\n231:     }{\n232:         {\n233:             name: \"valid spec with all required fields\",\n234:             spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n235:                 MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n236:                 SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n237:                 Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n238:             },\n239:             wantErr: false,\n240:         },\n241:         {\n242:             name: \"missing required maxSessionDuration\",\n243:             spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n244:                 SessionTimeout: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n245:                 Ports:          []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n246:             },\n247:             wantErr: true,\n248:         },\n249:     }\n250: \n251:     for _, tt := range tests {\n252:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n253:             // Validate using Kubernetes validation webhook or custom validation\n254:             err := validateAgentRuntimeSpec(tt.spec)\n255:             if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n256:                 t.Errorf(\"validateAgentRuntimeSpec() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n257:             }\n258:         })\n259:     }\n260: }\n261: ```\n262: \n263: #### DeepCopy Verification\n264: \n265: ```go\n266: func TestAgentRuntimeDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n267:     original := &AgentRuntime{\n268:         Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n269:             MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n270:             SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n271:             Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\"}},\n272:         },\n273:     }\n274: \n275:     copy := original.DeepCopy()\n276: \n277:     // Verify copy is independent\n278:     copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n279: \n280:     if original.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration == copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration {\n281:         t.Error(\"DeepCopy did not create independent copy\")\n282:     }\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ### Integration Tests\n287: \n288: #### CRD CRUD Operations\n289: \n290: ```go\n291: func TestAgentRuntimeCRUD(t *testing.T) {\n292:     // Requires kubeconfig or mock client\n293:     ctx := context.Background()\n294:     namespace := \"default\"\n295: \n296:     // Create\n297:     agentRuntime := &AgentRuntime{\n298:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n299:             Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n300:             Namespace: namespace,\n301:         },\n302:         Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n303:             MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n304:             SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n305:             Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n306:         },\n307:     }\n308: \n309:     created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n310:     require.NoError(t, err)\n311: \n312:     // Read\n313:     fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n314:     require.NoError(t, err)\n315:     assert.Equal(t, created.Spec.MaxSessionDuration, fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration)\n316: \n317:     // Update\n318:     fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n319:     updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n320:     require.NoError(t, err)\n321:     assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Hour, updated.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration)\n322: \n323:     // Delete\n324:     err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n325:     require.NoError(t, err)\n326: }\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### Schema Validation\n330: \n331: Verify generated CRD YAML matches expected OpenAPI v3 schema:\n332: \n333: ```bash\n334: # Generate CRDs\n335: make gen-crd\n336: \n337: # Validate against sample resources\n338: kubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/agentruntime.yaml\n339: kubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/codeinterpreter.yaml\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ## Dependencies\n343: \n344: | Package | Version | Role |\n345: |---------|---------|------|\n346: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | PodSpec, core types |\n347: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n348: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n349: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n350: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n351: \n352: ## Build Commands\n353: \n354: | Command | Description |\n355: |---------|-------------|\n356: | `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n357: | `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n358: | `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n359: | `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n364: \n365: ## Overview\n366: \n367: AR-003 focuses on the shared types and constants used across AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These shared definitions ensure consistency and reduce duplication across the API.\n368: \n369: ## Module Structure\n370: \n371: ```\n372: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n373: ├── doc.go                    # Package documentation + kubebuilder markers\n374: ├── register.go               # GroupVersion constants and scheme registration\n375: ├── types.go                  # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, shared types)\n376: ├── types_test.go             # Unit tests\n377: └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  # Auto-generated deepcopy methods\n378: ```\n379: \n380: ## Shared Constants\n381: \n382: ### Group Version\n383: \n384: ```go\n385: const (\n386:     GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n387:     Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n388: )\n389: \n390: var SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: GroupName, Version: Version}\n391: ```\n392: \n393: | Constant | Value | Description |\n394: |----------|-------|-------------|\n395: | `GroupName` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | API group name |\n396: | `Version` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | API version |\n397: | `SchemeGroupVersion` | `schema.GroupVersion` | Combined GroupVersion for scheme registration |\n398: \n399: ### Auth Modes\n400: \n401: ```go\n402: type AuthMode string\n403: \n404: const (\n405:     AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"  // picod authentication\n406:     AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"   // No authentication\n407: )\n408: ```\n409: \n410: | Constant | Value | Description |\n411: |----------|-------|-------------|\n412: | `AuthModePicod` | `\"picod\"` | Use picod for session authentication |\n413: | `AuthModeNone` | `\"none\"` | No authentication required |\n414: \n415: ## Shared Types\n416: \n417: ### TargetPort\n418: \n419: Defines port configuration for runtime services.\n420: \n421: ```go\n422: type TargetPort struct {\n423:     Port       int32  `json:\"port\"`        // Required: 1-65535\n424:     Protocol   string `json:\"protocol\"`    // Required: HTTP or HTTPS\n425:     Name       string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n426:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n427: }\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ### PodTemplateSpec\n431: \n432: Custom pod template for runtime pods.\n433: \n434: ```go\n435: type PodTemplateSpec struct {\n436:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n437:     Spec              *PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n438: }\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### PodSpec\n442: \n443: Selective subset of `corev1.PodSpec` for runtime customization.\n444: \n445: | Field | Type | Description |\n446: |-------|------|-------------|\n447: | `Containers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Container specifications |\n448: | `Volumes` | `[]corev1.Volume` | Pod volumes |\n449: | `RestartPolicy` | `corev1.RestartPolicy` | Container restart policy |\n450: | `ServiceAccountName` | `string` | Service account for pods |\n451: | `NodeSelector` | `map[string]string` | Node selection criteria |\n452: | `Affinity` | `*corev1.Affinity` | Pod scheduling affinity |\n453: | `Tolerations` | `[]corev1.Toleration` | Node taint tolerations |\n454: | `PriorityClassName` | `string` | Priority class |\n455: | `Priority` | `*int32` | Priority value |\n456: | `DNSPolicy` | `corev1.DNSPolicy` | DNS configuration |\n457: | `HostNetwork` | `bool` | Use host network |\n458: | `HostPID` | `bool` | Use host PID namespace |\n459: | `HostIPC` | `bool` | Use host IPC namespace |\n460: | `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.PodSecurityContext` | Pod security context |\n461: | `ImagePullSecrets` | `[]corev1.LocalObjectReference` | Image pull secrets |\n462: | `InitContainers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Init containers |\n463: \n464: ### ContainerSpec\n465: \n466: Selective subset of `corev1.Container`.\n467: \n468: | Field | Type | Description |\n469: |-------|------|-------------|\n470: | `Name` | `string` | Container name (Required) |\n471: | `Image` | `string` | Container image (Required) |\n472: | `Command` | `[]string` | Entrypoint command |\n473: | `Args` | `[]string` | Command arguments |\n474: | `Env` | `[]corev1.EnvVar` | Environment variables |\n475: | `Resources` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements` | Compute resources |\n476: | `ImagePullPolicy` | `corev1.PullPolicy` | Image pull policy |\n477: | `Ports` | `[]corev1.ContainerPort` | Exposed ports |\n478: | `LivenessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Liveness probe |\n479: | `ReadinessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Readiness probe |\n480: | `StartupProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Startup probe |\n481: | `VolumeMounts` | `[]corev1.VolumeMount` | Volume mounts |\n482: | `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.SecurityContext` | Container security context |\n483: \n484: ### ContainerTemplateSpec\n485: \n486: Simplified container spec for CodeInterpreter.\n487: \n488: ```go\n489: type ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n490:     Image            string                    `json:\"image\"` // Required\n491:     Command          []string                  `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n492:     Args             []string                  `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n493:     Env              []corev1.EnvVar           `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n494:     Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n495:     RuntimeClassName *string                   `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n496: }\n497: ```\n498: \n499: ## Scheme Registration\n500: \n501: ### Resource Helper\n502: \n503: ```go\n504: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n505:     return SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n506: }\n507: ```\n508: \n509: Returns `GroupResource` for RBAC and storage configuration.\n510: \n511: ### Type Registration\n512: \n513: ```go\n514: func AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n515:     scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion,\n516:         &AgentRuntime{},\n517:         &AgentRuntimeList{},\n518:         &CodeInterpreter{},\n519:         &CodeInterpreterList{},\n520:     )\n521:     metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n522:     return nil\n523: }\n524: ```\n525: \n526: ## Default Values\n527: \n528: | Field | Type | Default | Applied By |\n529: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n530: | `MaxSessionDuration` | `string` | `\"8h\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n531: | `SessionTimeout` | `string` | `\"15m\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n532: | `AuthMode` | `AuthMode` | `\"picod\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n533: | `WarmPoolSize` | `int32` | `0` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n534: \n535: ## Usage by CRDs\n536: \n537: ### AgentRuntime\n538: \n539: - Uses: `TargetPort`, `PodTemplateSpec`, `PodSpec`, `ContainerSpec`\n540: - Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`\n541: \n542: ### CodeInterpreter\n543: \n544: - Uses: `TargetPort`, `ContainerTemplateSpec`, `AuthMode`\n545: - Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`, `AuthModePicod`, `AuthModeNone`\n546: \n547: ## Code Generation\n548: \n549: Types are annotated with kubebuilder markers for code generation:\n550: \n551: ```go\n552: // +genclient\n553: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n554: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n555: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n556: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n557: ```\n558: \n559: | Marker | Purpose |\n560: |--------|---------|\n561: | `+genclient` | Generate typed client |\n562: | `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` | Generate list type |\n563: | `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` | Enable status subresource |\n564: | `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName` | CLI short name |\n565: | `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` | Custom columns |\n566: \n567: ## Validation\n568: \n569: Shared types use kubebuilder validation markers:\n570: \n571: | Validation | Marker | Applied To |\n572: |------------|--------|------------|\n573: | Required | `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` | Port, Protocol, Image |\n574: | Pattern | `+kubebuilder:validation:Pattern` | Duration strings |\n575: | Enum | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | AuthMode, Protocol |\n576: | Range | `+kubebuilder:validation:Minimum/Maximum` | Port number |\n577: | MinItems | `+kubebuilder:validation:MinItems` | TargetPorts array |\n\n(End of file - total 577 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- Go module path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs are defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically through the Kubernetes API server.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐\n│   API Server        │      │   Workload Manager  │\n│                     │      │                     │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  │      │  ┌───────────────┐  │\n│  │ agentruntimes │  │◄─────│  │ CREATE/UPDATE │  │\n│  └───────────────┘  │      │  └───────────────┘  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775841526676,"end":1775841526688}}}}
